{"id": "6894", "post": "<div class=\"post-6894 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-canada tag-kvm tag-lunanode-com tag-montreal tag-toronto\" id=\"post-6894\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/luna-node-now-available-in-montreal-openstack-kvm-from-3-60month/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Luna Node \u2013 Now available in Montreal \u2013 OpenStack KVM from $3.60/month</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/canada/\" rel=\"tag\">canada</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/kvm/\" rel=\"tag\">kvm</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/lunanode-com/\" rel=\"tag\">lunanode.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/montreal/\" rel=\"tag\">Montreal</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/toronto/\" rel=\"tag\">toronto</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> May 6, 2015 @ 1:00 pm, by Maarten Kossen</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"https://www.lunanode.com/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTc1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDE3NSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot alignnone size-medium wp-image-6897\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/lunanode-com-2015-05-06-06-16-39-300x175.png\" alt=\"lunanode com 2015-05-06 06-16-39\" width=\"300\" height=\"175\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/lunanode-com-2015-05-06-06-16-39-300x175.png 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/lunanode-com-2015-05-06-06-16-39-1024x597.png 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/lunanode-com-2015-05-06-06-16-39.png 1169w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a>Favyen, from <a href=\"https://www.lunanode.com/\">Luna Node</a>, has let us know that he has recently launched a second Canada location: Montreal! Montreal-based machines benefit from OVH\u2019s DDoS protection.</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>512MB KVM</strong><p></p><ul><li>512MB Memory</li><li>1 vCPU core</li><li>15GB HDD space</li><li>1TB traffic</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>KVM/Custom</li><li>$3.60/month</li><li><a href=\"https://dynamic.lunanode.com/register.php\">Sign up here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>1.5GB KVM</strong><p></p><ul><li>1.5GB Memory</li><li>1 vCPU core</li><li>15GB HDD space</li><li>2TB traffic</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>KVM/Custom</li><li>$5.18/month</li><li><a href=\"https://dynamic.lunanode.com/register.php\">Sign up here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>2GB KVM</strong><p></p><ul><li>2GB Memory</li><li>2 vCPU cores</li><li>20GB HDD space</li><li>2TB traffic</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>KVM/Custom</li><li>$7/month</li><li><a href=\"https://dynamic.lunanode.com/register.php\">Sign up here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>The above are example configurations; the 1.5GB and 2GB machines are specials.</em></p><p>Luna Node has been around for a while and started with a traditional SolusVM-based setup. Later, they switched to an OpenStack-based setup in Canada, offering a real cloud at LowEnd pricing. Features include actual hourly billing (like iwStack and EC2, not like DigitalOcean and Vultr), custom OS and templates, floating IP addresses, live snapshotting, an API, detachable volumes, private networking, and security groups. Luna Node is a registered company in British Columbia. They believe in free (as is freedom) and customer privacy; they offer the option to send GPG-encrypted e-mail and they published their <a href=\"https://github.com/uakfdotb/pybearmon\">distributed monitoring system</a> on GitHub). If you are a Luna Node customer, please let us know your experiences with their cloud!</p><p><span id=\"more-6894\"></span></p><p>Payments can be made via PayPal or BitCoin, as well as credit cards through PayPal. The first 20GB of image/volume storage is free. Private networks are $4/month. Nodes in Toronto have dual Intel Xeon L5639 CPUs and nodes in Montreal have an Intel Xeon E5-2650v2 CPU. Unfortunately, there\u2019s no IPv6 support yet. There\u2019s a minimum deposit amount of $12 which will be fully available as account credit. Before you order, please read their <a href=\"https://dynamic.lunanode.com/terms.php\">Terms of Service</a> and <a href=\"https://dynamic.lunanode.com/privacy.php\">Privacy Policy</a>.</p><p><strong>Network information</strong></p><p><span class=\"original\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Cogent DC \u2013 Toronto, Ontario, Canada</span><br>\nTest IPv4: 38.110.117.201<br>\nTest file: <a href=\"http://toronto-test.lunanode.com/100MB.test\">http://toronto-test.lunanode.com/100MB.test</a></span></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">OVH \u2013 Montreal, Quebec, Canada</span><br>\nTest IPv4: 167.114.196.211<br>\nTest file: <a href=\"http://montreal-test.lunanode.com/100MB.test\">http://montreal-test.lunanode.com/100MB.test</a></p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fluna-node-now-available-in-montreal-o